    • Method Detail

      • getOnlinePlayerIDs

        public static java.util.List<java.util.UUID> getOnlinePlayerIDs()
        Gets a list of the UUIDs of all currently online players.

        This will be a list of Mojang-provided UUIDs unless all of the following are not true:

        1. The server is in offline mode.
        2. The server does not have a properly configured proxy which supports IP and UUID forwarding when used in conjunction with this Bukkit implementation.
        If not all of these are true, the UUID will be calculated based on a hash of the username.

        If all of the above are true, the UUIDs returned by this method should be equivalent to those that would be returned from the Mojang account client utility.
        Returns:
        A mutable list of all of the unique identifiers of all of the players currently online on the Bukkit server.
        See Also:
        Server.getOnlinePlayers(), Entity.getUniqueId()
